00:30.800 --> 00:33.960
Want to take a walk with me?

01:16.360 --> 01:20.000
...continue to protest the presence
of a convicted sex offender

01:20.040 --> 01:22.400
in their neighborhood.
Michelle Betler reports.

01:22.440 --> 01:25.040
Thanks, Rick. I'm standing here
on Woodward Court,

01:25.080 --> 01:26.680
the quiet residential
street

01:26.720 --> 01:28.800
that has become
the focus of controversy

01:28.840 --> 01:31.920
ever since 48-year-old
Ronald James McGorvey returned here

01:31.960 --> 01:33.680
after serving a two-year
prison sentence

01:33.720 --> 01:35.680
for indecent exposure
to a minor.

01:35.720 --> 01:37.640
In the past few days
an organization

01:37.680 --> 01:39.720
known as the Committee
of Concerned Parents

01:39.760 --> 01:42.760
began distributing these notices
throughout the community

01:42.800 --> 01:44.960
warning neighbors
of what they call a quote,

01:45.000 --> 01:46.920
"Dangerous predator
in our midst."

01:46.960 --> 01:50.280
I don't really like having
him that close to my family.

01:50.320 --> 01:53.800
I think it's outrageous.
This block has too many children

01:53.880 --> 01:56.720
for a sex offender to, uh, be
moving in the neighborhood.

01:56.760 --> 01:58.520
I-- I don't think
it's a good idea.

01:58.560 --> 02:00.880
Makes me very nervous.
Makes me a little enraged.

02:00.920 --> 02:03.800
Um, I'd have a problem
if I see him on the street.

02:03.840 --> 02:06.000
It's like having an
alcoholic work in a bar.

02:06.000 --> 02:08.279
They don't mix.
They shouldn't be together.

02:08.320 --> 02:11.360
The conditions of his parole
expressly forbid McGorvey

02:11.400 --> 02:13.440
to be within 100 yards
of any playground,

02:13.480 --> 02:16.960
school or recreation area
where children normally gather.

02:17.000 --> 02:18.920
These conditions seem
to be of little comfort

02:18.960 --> 02:21.480
to the many parents whose
children play and go to school

02:21.520 --> 02:23.280
in this formerly
tranquil community,

02:23.280 --> 02:26.560
and who in the coming days and weeks
will be hoping for the best

02:26.600 --> 02:29.320
but preparing for the worst.
Rick, back to you.

02:38.680 --> 02:42.600
My husband and I had an
actual spiritual experience.

02:42.640 --> 02:45.720
We did this intense
spa treatment--

02:45.760 --> 02:47.360
- Oh, come on.
- No, listen to me.

02:47.400 --> 02:50.640
It was on our vacation in Cabo
and there were eight other couples

02:50.640 --> 02:52.720
and this Mayan woman.

02:52.760 --> 02:54.760
A goddess,
just a goddess.

02:54.800 --> 02:56.200
- She had--
- She's due in September.

02:56.240 --> 02:58.680
She thinks she's gonna
take three months off,

02:58.720 --> 03:01.240
then it's Christmas, then she'll be back
to work the first of the year.

03:01.280 --> 03:02.760
Please.

03:02.800 --> 03:05.680
Six months from now she'll be right here
on this bench with us.

03:05.680 --> 03:07.520
My friend Beth said
that the way she did it

03:07.560 --> 03:10.760
was to just take him with her every time
she went to the bathroom.

03:10.800 --> 03:13.720
- I find that strange.
- Yeah, that's what I said to Beth.

03:13.760 --> 03:15.120
It's Oedipal.

03:15.160 --> 03:17.040
What's the rush?

03:17.040 --> 03:20.040
Although I will say, when I was trying
to potty-train Christian,

03:20.080 --> 03:22.760
I opened the diaper
and it was huge!

03:22.800 --> 03:24.480
Like a grown man.

03:24.520 --> 03:28.000
Smiling politely to mask a
familiar feeling of desperation

03:28.040 --> 03:31.760
Sarah reminded herself to think
like an anthropologist.

03:31.800 --> 03:35.680
She was a researcher studying the
behavior of typical suburban women.

03:35.720 --> 03:37.200
They weren't organic?

03:37.240 --> 03:40.120
She was not a typical
suburban woman herself.

03:40.160 --> 03:42.320
Troy, stop that!

03:42.320 --> 03:43.760
Paul and I were having
sex the other night

03:43.760 --> 03:45.800
and I drifted off
right in the middle of it.

03:45.840 --> 03:47.600
It happens.

03:47.640 --> 03:50.640
Yeah, I guess.
But when I woke up and apologized

03:50.680 --> 03:52.440
he said he hadn't
even noticed.

03:52.480 --> 03:54.160
You know what
you should do?

03:54.160 --> 03:56.720
Set aside a specific
block of time for it.

03:56.760 --> 03:59.440
That's what Louis and I do--
every Tuesday night at 9:00.

03:59.480 --> 04:01.440
"Whether you want to or not"
Sarah thought,

04:01.480 --> 04:03.760
her eyes straying over
to the play area.

04:05.200 --> 04:07.880
Even at such a tiny
playground as this

04:07.920 --> 04:10.960
Lucy didn't interact much
with the other children.

04:11.000 --> 04:13.400
Sarah didn't really know why
they even bothered coming here,

04:13.440 --> 04:15.400
except that she'd
probably go crazy

04:15.440 --> 04:17.120
trapped in the house
all day

04:17.159 --> 04:19.240
with this unknowable
little person.

04:26.160 --> 04:27.920
Morning snack time
was 10:30 on the dot...

04:27.920 --> 04:30.080
Snack time!

04:30.120 --> 04:32.680
...a regimen established
and maintained by Mary Ann,

04:32.720 --> 04:35.280
who believed that rigid
adherence to a timetable

04:35.320 --> 04:37.160
was not only the key
to a healthy marriage,

04:37.200 --> 04:39.160
but to effective
parenting as well.

04:39.200 --> 04:41.680
- I'll take this one!
- I want that one!

04:43.760 --> 04:46.840
- Can I do it?
- Yeah. Ready?

04:49.640 --> 04:52.200
Mommy...

04:52.240 --> 04:54.120
where's my snack?

04:54.160 --> 04:56.440
I'm sorry, honey,
Mommy can't find it.

04:56.480 --> 04:58.640
- I forgot the rice cakes.
- Poor thing.

04:58.680 --> 05:00.680
- I'm sure it's in here somewhere.
- Second time this week.

05:00.720 --> 05:02.520
Well, who's going to keep
track of everything?

05:02.560 --> 05:04.720
- Bad mommy. Bad mommy.
- Just calm down, please.

05:04.760 --> 05:08.400
No calm down!
I want my snack!

05:08.400 --> 05:10.680
All right, you know what?
It's--

05:10.720 --> 05:13.480
it's just not here, okay?
See for yourself.

05:16.720 --> 05:18.320
Wait!

05:18.320 --> 05:21.160
Troy, honey,
give Lucy your goldfish.

05:21.200 --> 05:22.880
No!

05:22.920 --> 05:24.600
Troy Jonathan,
give me those goldfish!

05:24.640 --> 05:26.040
But, Mama, they're mine.

05:26.080 --> 05:28.520
No back talk.
You can share with your sister.

05:28.560 --> 05:30.680
Troy has goldfish for you.
Go sit down.

05:30.720 --> 05:32.760
That's much more than 10.

05:32.800 --> 05:35.160
- That's great.
- Look how big I made my lawn.

05:35.200 --> 05:37.600
Thank you, Mary Ann,
you're a life saver.

05:37.640 --> 05:40.840
It's nothing.
I just hate to see her suffer like that.

05:42.440 --> 05:44.880
Maybe you should make
a checklist and tape it to the door

05:44.920 --> 05:47.320
so it's the last thing you
see before leaving the house.

05:47.360 --> 05:49.400
That's what I do.

05:49.440 --> 05:53.040
Yeah, thank you. That's-- that's
a really helpful suggestion.

05:54.600 --> 05:56.080
You're welcome.

05:56.120 --> 05:58.240
Drink your juice.

05:58.280 --> 06:00.040
Are you the plane again?

06:00.080 --> 06:01.320
Look.

06:01.360 --> 06:03.720
Now you have to act like me.

06:03.760 --> 06:06.040
The prom king.

06:06.080 --> 06:09.480
Oh my God,
he's back.

06:09.520 --> 06:11.280
Sarah followed
the other women's gazes

06:11.280 --> 06:12.640
over to the entrance
of the playground,

06:12.680 --> 06:15.760
eager to finally get a glimpse
of the prom king,

06:15.800 --> 06:18.240
the handsome and mysterious
young father

06:18.280 --> 06:20.400
who had been a regular
at the Walker Street playground

06:20.400 --> 06:22.960
for several weeks
this past spring

06:23.000 --> 06:25.960
before abruptly
dropping out of sight.

06:26.000 --> 06:29.560
I don't need a rest.
I need an airplane ride.

06:29.600 --> 06:32.520
His departure had left a gaping
hole in the emotional lives

06:32.560 --> 06:34.880
of Cheryl, Theresa
and Mary Ann.

06:34.920 --> 06:37.880
Barely a day went by without one
of them speculating wistfully

06:37.920 --> 06:41.320
about the reason for his absence
and the likelihood of his return.

06:43.200 --> 06:47.280
Here I come.
There's no room for two of us, diesel.

06:47.280 --> 06:49.640
You've done it again.

06:49.680 --> 06:51.240
I hate steam engines.

06:51.280 --> 06:54.080
When I come back I will
pinch you with my pinchers.

06:54.120 --> 06:57.520
Yeah?
Well, when I come back

06:57.560 --> 06:59.200
I'm gonna ram you
with my rammer.

06:59.240 --> 07:01.040
- Ready?
- No, you won't.

07:03.440 --> 07:07.720
Every time you win,
diesel!

07:07.760 --> 07:10.520
I know.

07:10.560 --> 07:13.160
- Hello!
- Mommy's home.

07:13.200 --> 07:16.000
The jester's cap was something
that truly disturbed Brad.

07:16.040 --> 07:19.200
All day long the boy ate,
played and napped in it.

07:19.240 --> 07:23.080
But the moment his mother stepped in
the house he had no more use for it.

07:23.120 --> 07:25.400
As if the entire day
up to that point

07:25.440 --> 07:28.240
had been a pointless
and somewhat useless charade.

07:28.280 --> 07:30.320
You got some sun
today, didn't you?

07:30.360 --> 07:33.000
Did Daddy forget
the sunscreen again?

07:34.680 --> 07:37.320
What are you doing?

07:37.360 --> 07:40.680
That's his full name.
What's your favorite thing about him?

07:40.720 --> 07:43.080
Um...

07:43.120 --> 07:45.400
I like to come over
to his house.

07:45.440 --> 07:46.800
Hmm.

07:49.680 --> 07:53.000
I think I'm gonna finally break down
and get a cellphone.

07:53.040 --> 07:55.120
- Really?
- Mmm.

07:55.160 --> 07:56.560
Why?

07:59.760 --> 08:01.800
I have no way of reaching you
when I'm out with Aaron.

08:01.840 --> 08:03.120
You're done,
right?

08:05.240 --> 08:07.280
You've got one.

08:07.320 --> 08:09.200
Don't you think it's
strange that I don't?

08:09.200 --> 08:12.920
Yeah, I do.
You just never wanted one before.

08:12.960 --> 08:15.160
Yeah, I know.

08:15.200 --> 08:18.600
There's a family plan.
We can talk for free.

08:20.480 --> 08:22.160
Okay.

08:22.200 --> 08:24.680
Let's just see where we are
at the end of the month.

08:24.720 --> 08:26.280
Yeah?

08:26.320 --> 08:29.360
Are your hands okay?

08:43.960 --> 08:46.200
As was her custom each week
night after dinner,

08:46.240 --> 08:49.400
the boy's mother sent Brad
down to the municipal library

08:49.440 --> 08:52.400
to study for the bar exam.

08:52.440 --> 08:55.640
But he never quite made it through
the door of the building.

08:58.320 --> 09:01.640
Brad had been watching
the skateboarders for weeks now,

09:01.680 --> 09:04.120
sometimes for as long
as an hour at a stretch.

09:04.160 --> 09:07.200
But he never received the slightest
acknowledgement from any of them.

09:08.720 --> 09:12.520
He'd been the same age as these
boys when his mother died.

09:12.560 --> 09:14.600
- You do that!
- No way!

09:14.640 --> 09:16.640
- Nice.
- Hey, that was nice, dude!

09:16.680 --> 09:19.320
"I must have been like this,"
Brad sometimes thought.

09:19.360 --> 09:23.400
"I must have been
one of them."

09:26.760 --> 09:28.080
Awful.

09:29.880 --> 09:32.160
He should be castrated.

09:32.200 --> 09:33.840
Quick and clean,
just chop it off.

09:33.880 --> 09:36.080
Then you wouldn't have to worry
about notifying the neighbors.

09:36.080 --> 09:37.880
You know what else
you should do?

09:37.920 --> 09:40.840
Nail his penis above the entrance
to the elementary school.

09:40.880 --> 09:43.480
You know, as a warning
to other perverts.

09:43.520 --> 09:45.240
You think
this is funny?

09:45.280 --> 09:48.680
I just can't believe you want to
castrate a man for indecent exposure.

09:48.720 --> 09:51.440
My brother used
to expose himself when--

09:51.480 --> 09:53.840
when we were teenagers.
He'd do it in my bedroom,

09:53.840 --> 09:56.320
he'd do it in the dining room,
he'd do it in the back seat of a car.

09:56.360 --> 09:59.640
He'd always figure out a way to do it so
that nobody could see him except me.

09:59.680 --> 10:01.800
Didn't you
tell anyone?

10:01.840 --> 10:03.720
No, I didn't want
to get him in trouble.

10:03.760 --> 10:05.560
Maybe he should
be castrated.

10:07.360 --> 10:10.080
It's not the same thing.
He wasn't doing it to strangers.

10:10.120 --> 10:12.760
Oh my God, there he is.

10:12.800 --> 10:15.320
After all this time,
two days in a row.

10:15.360 --> 10:16.800
Where's the fire?

10:16.840 --> 10:19.400
Maybe he needed a vacation.

10:19.440 --> 10:21.760
From what?

10:21.800 --> 10:23.880
From being
the prom king.

10:23.920 --> 10:26.200
It's a dirty job,
but someone's gotta do it.

10:29.720 --> 10:31.840
- Close it?
- Close it.

10:31.880 --> 10:35.000
Close the gate.
There you go.

10:35.040 --> 10:37.480
- It's open.
- It's all right.

10:37.520 --> 10:40.520
- Somebody else will close it.
- Are we practicing?

10:42.640 --> 10:45.280
Are we playing
up on the swings?

10:45.320 --> 10:47.280
Swing time!

10:52.040 --> 10:53.800
What's he do for a living?

10:53.840 --> 10:57.400
We've never actually
spoken to him.

10:57.440 --> 10:58.760
Really?

10:58.800 --> 11:01.080
We don't even
know his name.

11:01.120 --> 11:04.120
I thought you guys said
he was a regular here.

11:04.160 --> 11:06.320
- It was awkward.
- He made us nervous.

11:06.320 --> 11:09.400
You had to think about what you
were gonna wear in the morning.

11:09.440 --> 11:12.000
You know, put on makeup.
It was exhausting.

11:20.880 --> 11:23.160
Mommy, push me!

11:23.200 --> 11:26.720
Okay.
I'll be right there.

11:29.760 --> 11:33.000
Wait!

11:33.040 --> 11:35.160
Five bucks if you get
his phone number.

11:41.680 --> 11:44.080
How old is she?

11:44.120 --> 11:45.560
Lucy,

11:45.600 --> 11:48.360
tell the nice boy
how old you are.

11:48.400 --> 11:50.720
I'm three.

11:50.760 --> 11:52.960
My grandma
lives in New Jersey.

11:53.000 --> 11:55.920
She doesn't have
a swim pool.

11:55.960 --> 11:57.480
Do you like to swim?

11:57.520 --> 12:00.720
I don't like sharks.
They eat you up.

12:00.720 --> 12:02.640
Don't listen to him.

12:02.680 --> 12:05.920
We go to the town pool
almost every day.

12:05.960 --> 12:09.360
- I'm Brad, by the way.
- Sarah.

12:09.400 --> 12:11.640
You guys come
here a lot?

12:11.680 --> 12:14.200
No, just the last
few weeks.

12:14.240 --> 12:16.400
I usually go to the one
over on Harris,

12:16.400 --> 12:18.640
with the big wood things,
you know, and the slide across.

12:18.640 --> 12:20.280
Yeah, we actually rent a house
right around the corner

12:20.320 --> 12:21.720
from there on Ashforth.

12:21.760 --> 12:24.640
That ice cream truck never leaves.
Such a nightmare.

12:24.680 --> 12:28.200
Yeah, tell me about it.

12:28.240 --> 12:30.880
You know, you're the first person
here who's ever talked to me.

12:32.680 --> 12:35.800
You make 'em nervous.

12:35.840 --> 12:38.320
Oh, right.

12:38.360 --> 12:41.560
I guess they don't see too many fathers
here during the weekdays.

12:44.840 --> 12:46.880
You don't have to be polite.
Go ahead and ask.

12:46.920 --> 12:48.720
What?

12:48.720 --> 12:51.800
You know, what the person who wears the
pants in the family does for a living.

12:51.840 --> 12:55.080
Oh. All right,
what does your wife do?

12:55.120 --> 12:58.400
- She makes documentaries.
- Oh, wow.

12:58.440 --> 13:01.200
- Like Michael Moore?
- Uh, like PBS.

13:01.240 --> 13:03.720
Oh.

13:03.760 --> 13:05.720
Well, I think it's
admirable you're here.

13:05.760 --> 13:08.480
There's no reason fathers
can't be primary caregivers.

13:10.920 --> 13:12.560
I finished law school
two years ago,

13:12.560 --> 13:15.920
but I can't seem to pass the bar exam.
Failed it twice now.

13:17.720 --> 13:20.520
Maybe you just don't
want to be a lawyer.

13:23.120 --> 13:24.880
I'll take the test
one more time.

13:24.920 --> 13:26.520
If I mess up now

13:26.560 --> 13:30.560
I'll just have to find something else
to do with my life.

13:30.600 --> 13:33.040
- Right, buddy?
- Right.

13:33.080 --> 13:36.240
Sarah was shocked by how Brad
delivered this confession,

13:36.240 --> 13:39.840
with no apparent sense of being in the
least bit embarrassed by his failure.

13:39.880 --> 13:42.440
Most men weren't like this.

13:42.480 --> 13:45.280
Her husband Richard
certainly wasn't.

13:45.320 --> 13:47.920
She wondered if Brad was
always this forthcoming.

13:47.920 --> 13:50.680
If anything,
he seemed a little lonely,

13:50.720 --> 13:54.120
all too ready to open his heart at
the slightest sign of interest,

13:54.160 --> 13:56.640
like a lot of young
mothers she knew.

13:56.680 --> 13:59.200
I couldn't help noticing
your stroller.

13:59.240 --> 14:01.400
Do you have
another child?

14:01.440 --> 14:04.160
No, just Aaron.
Got that at a yard sale.

14:04.200 --> 14:07.480
Extra seat comes in handy
for the bear, though.

14:07.520 --> 14:10.520
Lucy refuses to go
in a stroller or a car seat.

14:10.560 --> 14:13.840
We have to walk everywhere. It takes us
half an hour to go three blocks,

14:13.840 --> 14:15.520
unless I carry her.

14:15.560 --> 14:19.120
- Daddy, I'm finished.
- Are you sure? We just got here.

14:19.160 --> 14:21.640
I'm finished right now.

14:21.680 --> 14:24.200
Okay. All right,
here we go.

14:24.240 --> 14:27.200
Ready?
One, two, three.

14:27.240 --> 14:28.920
- Oops.
- Oh, hold on for a second.

14:28.960 --> 14:30.240
- There, thank you.
- Are you okay?

14:30.280 --> 14:32.080
No problem.

14:32.080 --> 14:35.080
It was then while watching Brad
kneel down at his son's feet

14:35.120 --> 14:39.760
that Sarah found herself gripped by
an unexpected pang of sadness.

14:39.760 --> 14:42.680
"Don't go," she thought.

14:42.720 --> 14:46.280
"Don't leave me here
with the others."

14:46.320 --> 14:50.000
- It was nice talking to you.
- Same here.

14:50.000 --> 14:53.080
Wait! Um...

14:53.120 --> 14:54.960
Come here. Just...

14:55.000 --> 14:57.000
come here.

14:59.080 --> 15:01.000
You see those women
over there?

15:01.040 --> 15:03.040
Just, yeah, don't--
don't look.

15:03.080 --> 15:05.840
You know what
they call you?

15:05.880 --> 15:07.200
What?

15:07.240 --> 15:09.440
The prom king.

15:09.480 --> 15:11.080
Oh God, really?

15:11.120 --> 15:13.480
Yeah, they mean it
as a compliment.

15:13.520 --> 15:15.880
You're a big character
in their fantasy lives.

15:15.920 --> 15:17.320
Wow.

15:17.360 --> 15:20.560
Um, so one of them bet me $5
I couldn't get your phone number.

15:20.560 --> 15:23.240
Five bucks, huh?

15:23.280 --> 15:25.080
Yeah.

15:25.120 --> 15:27.440
Could we split
it 50-50?

15:27.440 --> 15:29.440
It could be
arranged.

15:29.480 --> 15:30.880
It doesn't have to be
your real number.

15:30.920 --> 15:33.440
Oh, well, you know, in that case, sure.
You got a pen?

15:33.480 --> 15:36.600
Great. Oh shit, no I--
um, no I don't.

15:36.640 --> 15:38.480
- Uh...
- Well...

15:38.520 --> 15:40.520
No wait, just--
wait.

15:40.560 --> 15:43.720
You know what'd
really be funny?

15:43.760 --> 15:46.640
If you gave me a hug.

15:46.680 --> 15:49.880
- You think?
- Yeah.

15:49.920 --> 15:52.240
- Yeah.
- All right, come here.

15:53.440 --> 15:55.680
Oh my God.

15:57.160 --> 16:00.320
Do you want to really
freak them out?

16:00.360 --> 16:01.720
Yeah.

16:01.760 --> 16:03.680
Who's gonna talk in there?

16:05.640 --> 16:06.720
- Oh my God!
- Troy!

16:06.760 --> 16:08.240
- Lucy!
- Isabelle!

16:08.280 --> 16:10.960
Isabelle! Come here, Isabelle.
Okay, we have to go.

16:10.960 --> 16:12.760
- Isabelle!
- Troy!

16:12.800 --> 16:15.760
