I mean, I think.

36:53.360 --> 36:55.360
E-eight.

37:35.640 --> 37:37.280
You want to go
in the pool?

37:37.320 --> 37:38.880
You do?

37:41.840 --> 37:45.080
One, two.

37:50.720 --> 37:53.600
Daddy, can I go
in the pool now?

37:53.640 --> 37:55.480
In a minute, okay?

37:55.520 --> 37:58.560
Okay.

37:58.600 --> 38:01.360
There you go.

38:08.360 --> 38:10.800
Mommy, I have
to go pee-pee.

38:10.840 --> 38:13.040
Just go in the pool.

38:13.080 --> 38:16.360
Huh-uh, I want
to go to the bathroom.

38:16.400 --> 38:18.240
Really?

38:18.280 --> 38:20.080
Okay, come on.

38:24.560 --> 38:26.120
Okay, ready?

38:26.160 --> 38:28.200
There.

38:55.960 --> 38:58.000
Swing down.

39:00.880 --> 39:03.760
Hey, I'm drumming it.

39:03.800 --> 39:05.000
Oh.

39:05.960 --> 39:08.800
Wow.

39:08.840 --> 39:11.280
- It's you.
- Yeah, hey.

39:11.320 --> 39:13.960
- Hi!
- Okay.

39:15.320 --> 39:17.680
I hope you don't mind.
Lucy has sensitive skin.

39:17.720 --> 39:20.280
She's better off
in the shade.

39:20.320 --> 39:22.920
Oh no,
not at all.

39:22.960 --> 39:24.160
It's nice
to see you again.

39:24.200 --> 39:26.120
Yeah, you too.

39:28.640 --> 39:30.960
I'm sorry,
would you get my back?

39:31.000 --> 39:34.000
Um...
okay, sure.

39:34.040 --> 39:35.360
Thanks.

39:35.400 --> 39:36.880
Right.

39:36.920 --> 39:39.840
# Who is knocking
on the door? #

39:39.880 --> 39:41.320
- Thanks a lot.
- # Knocking on the door #

39:41.360 --> 39:43.400
# Knocking on the door #

39:43.440 --> 39:46.040
- # Who is knocking on the door? #
- It's okay, just...

39:46.080 --> 39:48.440
# A way, hey hey. #

39:48.480 --> 39:50.520
Lucy, say hi to the little boy
from the playground.

39:50.560 --> 39:54.280
Hi.

39:54.320 --> 39:56.480
You remember him?

40:01.520 --> 40:03.440
The pool became a ritual.

40:03.480 --> 40:06.080
I was trying to think.
I just didn't know the way.

40:06.120 --> 40:07.840
- Oh oh, okay.
- I'm here, I'm here.

40:07.880 --> 40:09.480
We have the creature
and we have flower.

40:09.520 --> 40:10.680
Right.

40:10.720 --> 40:13.120
Day after day they sat
together in the shade

40:13.160 --> 40:15.080
getting to know
each other.

40:16.120 --> 40:18.840
This needs mustard.

40:18.880 --> 40:21.040
- Mustard?
- Yeah.

40:21.080 --> 40:22.920
Having little choice
in the matter,

40:22.960 --> 40:24.720
Aaron and Lucy formed
a fragile friendship.

40:30.720 --> 40:32.640
Aw, that's perfect.

40:32.680 --> 40:35.480
Sometimes Brad and Sarah
traded offspring.

40:39.400 --> 40:41.440
Mama said, "What Papa
told you was right.

40:41.480 --> 40:44.400
It's not a good idea
to talk to strangers."

40:44.440 --> 40:48.240
It was the most fun
Sarah had had in years.

41:01.240 --> 41:04.160
But there was always
that longing to touch,

41:04.200 --> 41:07.560
to be touched by Brad.

41:07.600 --> 41:11.000
And, as badly as
she wanted this,

41:11.040 --> 41:14.360
she wanted just as badly
to hold on to the innocent public life

41:14.400 --> 41:16.840
they'd made for themselves
out in the open.

41:16.880 --> 41:19.400
So she accepted
the trade--

41:19.440 --> 41:22.400
the melancholy
handshake at 4:00

41:22.440 --> 41:25.400
in exchange for this
little patch of grass,

41:25.440 --> 41:27.960
some sunscreen
and companionship.

41:28.000 --> 41:31.360
One more happy day
at the pool.

41:33.000 --> 41:35.600
Okay, no pasta
for dinner, okay?

41:35.640 --> 41:37.920
We eat way too much
pasta around here.

41:37.960 --> 41:39.880
I thought you
liked my pasta.

41:39.920 --> 41:42.400
No, I do.
That's the problem.

41:42.440 --> 41:45.280
Pretty soon I can sell advertising
space on my ass.

41:46.480 --> 41:47.920
No, that's okay.
I've got to go.

41:47.960 --> 41:49.840
I've got
a 9:00 at Taps.

41:49.880 --> 41:51.880
I thought you were
already editing.

41:51.920 --> 41:54.680
Yeah, so did I.
It was just--

41:54.720 --> 41:58.120
there's something in this
family's story that really got to me.

42:00.680 --> 42:02.800
The father was...

42:02.840 --> 42:05.680
K-I-L-L-E-D

42:05.680 --> 42:08.960
in a, um,
mortar attack,

42:09.000 --> 42:11.760
and, um, left behind
a little boy.

42:14.280 --> 42:16.680
I was talking to the mother the other
day on the phone,

42:16.720 --> 42:20.320
and she was saying she didn't know what
she was going to do next Christmas.

42:20.360 --> 42:21.600
Jeez, I bet.

42:21.640 --> 42:24.040
No, it wasn't like that.
It was more...

42:24.080 --> 42:26.960
she was wondering, should she keep
this tradition with her son

42:26.960 --> 42:28.600
that began with
the boy's father.

42:28.640 --> 42:31.320
And she was saying
he had this knack

42:31.360 --> 42:33.960
for requesting
odd Christmas gifts--

42:34.000 --> 42:35.880
scuba gear one year

42:35.920 --> 42:38.440
and rappelling gear
the next.

42:38.480 --> 42:42.280
She said he wasn't
afraid to try anything.

42:42.320 --> 42:44.840
Trying new things
made him feel...

42:44.880 --> 42:47.760
more alive.

42:49.680 --> 42:52.840
I've got to go.
See you later.

43:01.360 --> 43:04.360
Patch one of your best
and then we'll patch both of them.

43:04.400 --> 43:06.240
Okay?

43:08.880 --> 43:11.200
Hey, I got something.

43:15.400 --> 43:17.800
Hot enough for you?

43:17.840 --> 43:20.360
Yeah.

43:20.400 --> 43:23.360
Yeah, it's so humid.

43:23.400 --> 43:26.760
I've got football
practice tonight.

43:26.800 --> 43:28.680
Be like playing
in a sauna.

43:28.720 --> 43:31.920
Watch out for
that Italian guy.

43:31.920 --> 43:34.440
What's his name?

43:34.480 --> 43:35.800
Corrente?

43:35.840 --> 43:38.440
Yeah.

43:38.480 --> 43:40.840
Remember what
happened to your knee last week?

43:40.880 --> 43:43.240
You should be
careful, Brad.

43:45.920 --> 43:47.560
I'll be careful.

43:47.600 --> 43:50.120
Promise?

43:52.360 --> 43:55.960
Yeah.
Yeah, I promise.

43:58.960 --> 44:01.360
Weatherman said
scattered showers.

44:01.360 --> 44:03.280
I don't see
scattered showers.

44:12.960 --> 44:15.720
Mom, could I please
have some money for a snack?

44:15.760 --> 44:18.240
No, sweetheart.
You guys just had a snack. No.

44:18.280 --> 44:19.680
Oh, okay.

44:19.720 --> 44:21.600
All they want is sugar.

44:21.640 --> 44:23.360
Constantly.

45:38.040 --> 45:39.960
Oh, no.

45:46.800 --> 45:49.280
It's him.

45:50.360 --> 45:52.280
Oh, Jesus.

45:59.480 --> 46:01.480
Oh my God,
it's him.

46:01.520 --> 46:04.040
He's in the pool.

46:04.080 --> 46:06.120
Oh my God!

46:06.160 --> 46:08.200
Jacob, get out
of the pool now!

46:08.240 --> 46:10.160
Oh my God.
That's him.

46:10.200 --> 46:14.000
- Get away from that man.
- Why is everybody running to the pool?

46:14.040 --> 46:15.960
Brooke?
Jake?

46:16.000 --> 46:18.600
Dale, you'd better
get over here.

46:22.560 --> 46:23.920
Get out of the pool!

46:33.360 --> 46:36.080
Where's your sister?

46:44.440 --> 46:47.960
Why'd we have to get out, Mom?

46:48.000 --> 46:50.680
I'm scared.

46:55.800 --> 46:58.760
- What did he do?
- What's going on?

47:13.680 --> 47:16.240
I'm scared.

47:21.440 --> 47:24.080
Um, why the
police is here?

47:24.120 --> 47:27.720
Um, there's a man over there who
doesn't have a ticket to get in,

47:28.040 --> 47:29.640
so they're asking
him to go home.

47:29.680 --> 47:31.640
Mr. McGorvey.
Mr. McGorvey.

47:31.680 --> 47:33.480
It'd be wise for you to get
out of the pool at this time.

47:41.320 --> 47:43.320
Did that man
go near you?

47:43.360 --> 47:45.960
You're sure he
didn't touch you?

47:50.080 --> 47:52.360
Step out of
the pool, sir.

48:10.800 --> 48:13.800
I was only trying
to cool off.

48:13.840 --> 48:17.160
All right,
let's go.

48:21.520 --> 48:24.400
You can go back in the pool.

48:56.120 --> 48:59.560
Bear with us, please. You
know what that sounds means.

48:59.600 --> 49:02.880
Let's go. Out of the pool.
We're closing her up. Let's go.

49:02.960 --> 49:05.800
Exit the pool and vacate
the grounds immediately.

49:05.840 --> 49:07.760
Okay, I'll see
you tomorrow.

49:07.760 --> 49:10.200
You're going to carry her?
Come on, put her in the stroller.

49:10.240 --> 49:11.400
No, she won't do the stroller.

49:11.440 --> 49:12.680
- Really?
- No, she will not do this.

49:12.720 --> 49:13.960
Lucy, would you like to go
in the stroller?

49:14.000 --> 49:16.560
Can I interest you in a stroller?
It appears she'd like a stroller.

49:18.000 --> 49:19.880
It's out of
your way.

49:19.920 --> 49:23.000
No, it's fine.
You don't mind, do you, Aaron?

49:23.040 --> 49:25.320
Run!

49:35.280 --> 49:37.880
You'd better come inside.
You can't walk home in this.

49:40.160 --> 49:41.760
Oh!

49:49.840 --> 49:53.240
- You can put him down in Lucy's room.
- Okay.

49:57.800 --> 49:59.680
This is amazing.

49:59.720 --> 50:02.280
She never naps.

50:02.320 --> 50:04.520
Well, he'll be
out for the next two hours.

50:04.560 --> 50:07.080
We'll have to get him out
of that nightgown, though,

50:07.120 --> 50:09.160
before he wakes up
or he'll never forgive me.

50:19.040 --> 50:20.920
Nice place.

50:20.960 --> 50:22.600
- You think so?
- Yeah.

50:22.640 --> 50:24.440
Well, Richard does
all right for himself.

50:24.480 --> 50:26.400
What's he do, again?

50:26.480 --> 50:29.920
Lies. Um, please have a seat.
Make yourself comfortable.

50:29.960 --> 50:31.560
Better not,
I might ruin your furniture.

50:31.600 --> 50:34.360
I'll put these things in the dryer
and get us some towels.

50:34.400 --> 50:36.040
Okay.

52:34.680 --> 52:37.560
Oh, God!

52:39.440 --> 52:41.720
Oh, God!

52:46.160 --> 52:48.480
Do you feel bad
about this?

52:48.520 --> 52:50.920
No, I don't.

52:50.960 --> 52:52.800
I do.

52:52.840 --> 52:55.480
I feel really bad.

52:55.520 --> 52:57.040
Okay.

53:30.760 --> 53:33.600
Son?

53:37.000 --> 53:39.000
Son?

53:42.160 --> 53:44.560
Be well.

53:49.400 --> 53:51.080
May knew it wasn't natural

53:51.120 --> 53:52.920
for a grown man
to be living with his mother.

53:52.960 --> 53:54.880
No hobbies,
no diversions.

53:54.920 --> 53:57.720
It was like he was
still in prison.

53:57.760 --> 53:59.640
What he needed
was a girlfriend,

53:59.680 --> 54:02.280
and May intended to
help him find one.

54:02.320 --> 54:05.400
There are four whole columns
of lonely women here,

54:05.440 --> 54:07.840
and only a handful of men.
The odds are on our side.

54:07.880 --> 54:10.240
Why wouldn't one of
these women want

54:10.280 --> 54:12.840
to meet a nice
person like you?

54:12.880 --> 54:15.240
I'm not
a nice person.

54:15.280 --> 54:17.640
You did a bad thing.

54:17.680 --> 54:19.920
But that doesn't mean
you're a bad person.

54:19.960 --> 54:22.240
I have a psychosexual
disorder.

54:22.280 --> 54:23.680
You're better now.

54:23.720 --> 54:25.600
They wouldn't have let
you out if you weren't.

54:25.640 --> 54:27.880
They let me out
because they had to.

54:27.920 --> 54:30.400
Well, maybe
if you found

54:30.440 --> 54:32.640
a girlfriend closer
to your own age

54:32.680 --> 54:35.400
you wouldn't have
the bad urges so often.

54:35.440 --> 54:37.960
I don't want a girlfriend
my own age, Mommy.

54:38.000 --> 54:40.520
I wish I did.

54:43.320 --> 54:45.280
What are you going
to do when I'm gone?

54:45.360 --> 54:47.720
Who's going to
take care of you?

54:50.800 --> 54:52.720
What's the matter,
Mommy?

54:55.600 --> 54:57.520
Are you sick
or something?

54:57.520 --> 54:59.920
I'm an old woman.
I'm not going to live forever,

54:59.920 --> 55:01.960
Who's going to cook
for you?

55:02.000 --> 55:03.640
Who's going
to wash the dishes?

55:03.680 --> 55:06.080
I can wash
the dishes,

55:06.160 --> 55:07.960
You've never washed
a dish in your life.

55:08.000 --> 55:10.600
I could do it if I had to.
I'm not a retard.

55:10.640 --> 55:13.080
No, you're not.

55:14.560 --> 55:17.080
You're a miracle,
Ronnie.

55:18.840 --> 55:21.640
We're all miracles.

55:21.680 --> 55:24.320
You know why?

55:24.360 --> 55:26.440
Because as humans,

55:26.480 --> 55:30.240
everyday we go
about our business,

55:30.280 --> 55:32.800
and all that time

55:32.840 --> 55:35.680
we know, we all know

55:35.720 --> 55:38.840
that the things
we love,

55:38.880 --> 55:42.400
the people we love...

55:44.400 --> 55:47.960
at any time, it can
all be taken away.

55:51.760 --> 55:54.560
We live knowing that

55:54.600 --> 55:57.520
and we keep
going anyway.

56:02.800 --> 56:05.200
Animals don't do that.

56:09.480 --> 56:12.480
Now I'm not asking you
to get married, Ronnie.

56:14.160 --> 56:17.360
I'm just saying put an ad in the paper,
see what happens.

56:17.400 --> 56:20.680
Fine. I'll do it if
it will make you happy.

56:20.720 --> 56:23.080
But just one date.
All right?

56:26.160 --> 56:28.960
You have a nice smile,
why don't we start with that?

56:29.000 --> 56:32.080
What else?

56:34.320 --> 56:37.280
You always eat what I put in front
of you. You never complain.

56:37.320 --> 56:40.040
What else?

56:40.080 --> 56:41.800
You're trying to
get back in shape.

56:41.840 --> 56:43.560
You exercise.

56:54.280 --> 56:56.160
Wait right there,
young man.

56:56.200 --> 56:58.480
If you're going out
for some exercise,

56:58.520 --> 57:01.120
you can post this now.

57:03.760 --> 57:06.160
Hmm.

57:36.880 --> 57:38.800
Mmm.

57:41.520 --> 57:43.800
Come on.

57:43.840 --> 57:45.400
Let's do it again.

57:47.920 --> 57:50.120
All right.

57:51.240 --> 57:53.800
God, it's hot
as hell up here.

57:53.840 --> 57:55.960
What's wrong with
the laundry room?

57:56.000 --> 57:59.040
No mattress.

57:59.080 --> 58:02.160
Come on.
Lie down.

58:16.400 --> 58:18.320
You're nervous,
aren't you?

58:18.320 --> 58:20.120
What?
What do you mean?

58:20.160 --> 58:21.960
The game.

58:22.000 --> 58:26.320
Don't worry.
You'll be great tonight.

58:27.760 --> 58:30.800
I don't know.
I haven't played in 10 years.

58:32.760 --> 58:35.400
It used to be
my whole life.

58:35.440 --> 58:38.120
Then when I stopped,
I just...

58:38.160 --> 58:41.280
stopped. I didn't
even miss it.

58:42.840 --> 58:45.200
Now that I'm playing
again, I...

58:45.240 --> 58:47.880
feel I--

58:49.640 --> 58:52.120
I don't know.

58:52.160 --> 58:54.080
You feel alive.

58:54.120 --> 58:55.480
Yeah.

58:55.520 --> 58:58.040
That's good.

58:58.080 --> 58:59.960
That's how you're
supposed to feel.

59:01.120 --> 59:03.400
You're right.

59:03.440 --> 59:06.600
I guess it's just
been awhile.

59:08.000 --> 59:10.360
Yeah.

59:54.960 --> 59:56.880
Shake.

01:00:17.480 --> 01:00:19.560
- Call it.
- Heads.

01:00:21.000 --> 01:00:23.160
Heads it is.

01:00:25.720 --> 01:00:27.800
Ready?

01:00:36.360 --> 01:00:38.800
- Hello?
- Hi, Mom. Did I wake you?

01:00:38.840 --> 01:00:40.680
Oh, no honey.
Is everything okay?

01:00:40.720 --> 01:00:42.440
Yeah, I'm fine.

01:00:42.480 --> 01:00:44.000
You don't
sound fine.

01:00:44.040 --> 01:00:46.400
No, there's nothing wrong.
I just wanted to say hi.

01:00:46.480 --> 01:00:48.760
Well, hi.

01:00:48.800 --> 01:00:50.200
Hi.

01:00:50.240 --> 01:00:51.640
So how's my
little guy?

01:00:51.680 --> 01:00:53.880
He's great.
He's sleeping right here next to me.

01:00:53.920 --> 01:00:55.520
He's such
a cutie.

01:00:55.560 --> 01:00:57.440
So where's Brad?

01:00:57.480 --> 01:00:59.560
Brad's out.

01:00:59.600 --> 01:01:02.200
Oh, I'm surprised
the library stays open this late.

01:01:02.240 --> 01:01:03.880
Well, he's not
at the library.

01:01:03.920 --> 01:01:05.440
He's playing football
with some buddies.

01:01:05.520 --> 01:01:08.200
Oh, honey. Do you remember when
your father took up golf?

01:01:08.240 --> 01:01:10.760
He's not
like dad.

01:01:10.800 --> 01:01:13.160
Honey, they're
all the same.

01:01:13.200 --> 01:01:15.320
Well, he's not.

01:01:15.360 --> 01:01:18.280
You work so hard.

01:01:18.320 --> 01:01:20.520
Now listen...

01:01:20.560 --> 01:01:22.960
I could keep an eye
on the boys when you're at work;

01:01:23.000 --> 01:01:24.440
make sure they're
staying out of trouble.

01:01:24.480 --> 01:01:26.760
- Do you want me to come up for a visit?
- No no, Mom, don't come.

01:01:26.800 --> 01:01:28.200
Well, honey, I worry
about you kids.

01:01:28.240 --> 01:01:30.480
Now what are you going to do if he
fails the test again?

01:01:30.520 --> 01:01:31.920
He's not going
to fail the test.

01:01:31.960 --> 01:01:33.680
Oh, honey,
that's what you said last time.

01:01:33.720 --> 01:01:35.400
Now how are you
doing for money?

01:01:35.440 --> 01:01:37.880
We're fine.

01:01:37.920 --> 01:01:41.000
I'm going to send you a little
extra this month.

01:01:41.040 --> 01:01:42.600
- Mom...
- Honey, it's no burden.

01:01:42.640 --> 01:01:45.800
- Mom... Mom, please.
- I'm happy to help.

01:01:50.640 --> 01:01:53.320
Aw, shit.

01:01:59.040 --> 01:02:01.280
Although the Guardians
lost by 26 points,

01:02:01.320 --> 01:02:04.160
Brad felt oddly exhilarated in the bar
after the game.

01:02:06.000 --> 01:02:09.080
He could feel a new respect
in the way the cops looked at him.

01:02:09.120 --> 01:02:12.160
- What you drinking, buddy?
- He wasn't on probation anymore.

01:02:12.200 --> 01:02:13.360
He was a member
of the team.

01:02:13.400 --> 01:02:15.040
Ice and Advil.

01:02:15.080 --> 01:02:17.320
If all else fails, you can always see
the team physician,

01:02:17.360 --> 01:02:19.600
Dr. Daniels.
All his friends call him Jack.

01:02:19.640 --> 01:02:21.800
- To the good doctor.
- Hear, hear.

01:02:24.760 --> 01:02:27.640
- Larry? Here, you go Larry.
- Oh, thanks.

01:02:27.680 --> 01:02:29.680
Let me just
grab a chair.

01:02:35.520 --> 01:02:39.120
Oh, we just gave you a shot.
We just gave you a shot.

01:02:46.960 --> 01:02:49.840
I had no business being
on that field tonight.

01:02:49.880 --> 01:02:52.080
I let you down.

01:02:52.120 --> 01:02:53.600
I let the whole
team down.

01:02:53.680 --> 01:02:55.400
I'm slow and
I'm fat.

01:02:55.440 --> 01:02:57.280
I let that guy
piss all over me.

01:02:57.320 --> 01:02:59.880
Come on. That guy was offsides
the whole night.

01:03:03.240 --> 01:03:05.880
Joanie left me.

01:03:05.920 --> 01:03:08.800
Took the kids and went
to her mother's.

