01:20:28.320 --> 01:20:30.240
Well, I have a good
feeling about this whole thing.

01:20:30.280 --> 01:20:33.120
In fact, I think I'm gonna go buy
a bottle of champagne

01:20:33.160 --> 01:20:35.400
and put it in the fridge,
and we can open it to celebrate

01:20:35.440 --> 01:20:37.880
when we get
the good news.

01:20:37.920 --> 01:20:40.800
Don't get your hopes up.

01:20:40.840 --> 01:20:42.760
We've been
through this before.

01:20:42.760 --> 01:20:45.640
Huh-uh. This time's
gonna be different.

01:20:45.680 --> 01:20:47.680
I can feel it.

01:21:16.960 --> 01:21:20.200
Can you believe it?
This is our first date.

01:21:20.240 --> 01:21:23.360
Like a date, you know,
without the kids, I mean.

01:21:23.400 --> 01:21:26.480
How was Lucy?
Did she cry or anything?

01:21:26.520 --> 01:21:28.600
No, are you kidding?

01:21:28.640 --> 01:21:31.280
With Jean there, she
just about shoved me out the door.

01:21:35.600 --> 01:21:39.360
I thought we could make something
really beautiful.

01:21:39.400 --> 01:21:42.440
I have so
many things here.

01:21:42.440 --> 01:21:45.000
We could make...

01:21:45.040 --> 01:21:47.280
a picture frame.

01:21:48.760 --> 01:21:52.600
Or a jewelry box.

01:21:53.640 --> 01:21:57.480
Or a hat.

01:21:59.400 --> 01:22:02.440
Something for my mommy.

01:22:02.440 --> 01:22:04.360
Okay.

01:22:07.080 --> 01:22:08.440
- Stop it, stop it.
- No, Ronnie.

01:22:08.480 --> 01:22:11.000
Ron-- Ron-- Ronnie,
just hold on.

01:22:11.040 --> 01:22:14.080
Now there.

01:22:14.120 --> 01:22:17.440
You look handsome.
She won't be disappointed.

01:22:17.480 --> 01:22:20.360
Wait'll she hears
about my criminal record.

01:22:20.400 --> 01:22:22.600
I don't think you need
to get into that just yet.

01:22:22.640 --> 01:22:24.800
Why don't you stick
to small talk?

01:22:24.840 --> 01:22:27.680
What if someone
recognizes me?

01:22:27.720 --> 01:22:31.040
That's highly unlikely.
I made the dinner reservation

01:22:31.080 --> 01:22:33.440
at a restaurant over
in Haverhill.

01:22:49.640 --> 01:22:51.560
Sheila.

01:22:53.880 --> 01:22:56.120
- Sheila.
- Yeah.

01:22:59.440 --> 01:23:01.800
Something wrong
with the food?

01:23:03.320 --> 01:23:05.520
No, it's fine.

01:23:05.560 --> 01:23:09.320
Back at the house you
mentioned you were on medication.

01:23:11.600 --> 01:23:15.000
- What kind?
- All kinds.

01:23:15.040 --> 01:23:16.960
Mostly psychotropic.

01:23:19.920 --> 01:23:23.240
So you had some kind
of a breakdown?

01:23:23.240 --> 01:23:26.880
Mm-hmm, my junior year
in college.

01:23:26.920 --> 01:23:28.880
You were that young?

01:23:30.800 --> 01:23:32.840
What happened?

01:23:32.880 --> 01:23:35.480
I don't really know.

01:23:35.520 --> 01:23:38.560
Well, nervous breakdowns
don't just come out of nowhere.

01:23:39.760 --> 01:23:42.040
Something must have
caused it.

01:23:42.080 --> 01:23:44.600
I guess.

01:23:44.640 --> 01:23:47.480
But I was fine before
I left for college.

01:23:49.000 --> 01:23:51.280
I don't know.
Maybe it was the stress

01:23:51.320 --> 01:23:53.080
of being on my own.

01:23:53.120 --> 01:23:55.760
Maybe it's a chemical
imbalance in my brain.

01:23:55.800 --> 01:23:58.920
Every psychiatrist I go to
has a different opinion.

01:23:58.960 --> 01:24:02.000
This one guy, Dr. Faris,

01:24:02.040 --> 01:24:05.680
he said I must have been
sexually abused as a child.

01:24:05.720 --> 01:24:07.200
When I told him
I wasn't,

01:24:07.240 --> 01:24:09.720
he said I must be
repressing the memory.

01:24:09.760 --> 01:24:13.400
Right, um, so what
happened after that?

01:24:13.440 --> 01:24:15.240
Did you drop out
of school?

01:24:15.240 --> 01:24:17.960
Not right away.

01:24:18.000 --> 01:24:20.080
My mother wanted me
to go

01:24:20.120 --> 01:24:22.080
to the campus
counseling center.

01:24:22.120 --> 01:24:24.560
And they wanted
the problem fixed, like I could just

01:24:24.600 --> 01:24:27.400
snap my fingers and everything
would be okay again.

01:24:27.440 --> 01:24:29.800
Yeah, I know
all about that.

01:24:29.800 --> 01:24:33.160
You do?

01:24:33.200 --> 01:24:36.560
Yes, I do.

01:24:39.560 --> 01:24:43.120
So they said
I could leave school

01:24:43.160 --> 01:24:45.760
and get married and have lots of kids
like my sisters,

01:24:45.800 --> 01:24:47.840
and I can't take care
of kids.

01:24:47.880 --> 01:24:50.120
I can't even take care
of myself

01:24:50.160 --> 01:24:53.200
most of the time.
Besides, who's gonna marry me?

01:24:53.240 --> 01:24:56.520
You're not so bad.

01:24:56.560 --> 01:24:58.520
What?

01:24:59.680 --> 01:25:02.120
You're--
you're not so bad.

01:25:07.720 --> 01:25:10.080
I haven't had
a real boyfriend in six years,

01:25:10.120 --> 01:25:13.000
not since my second
breakdown.

01:25:13.040 --> 01:25:15.720
I had this thing happen
on a Greyhound bus.

01:25:15.720 --> 01:25:18.720
- I was--
- Do you want me to wrap that up?

01:25:18.760 --> 01:25:21.400
Oh, no, thank you.

01:25:21.440 --> 01:25:24.160
No, wrap it up, please.
I'll take it home.

01:25:24.200 --> 01:25:26.720
Folks gonna want dessert?

01:25:26.760 --> 01:25:29.720
What do you say, Sheila?
You wanna share something sweet?

01:25:34.560 --> 01:25:36.880
Let's make a little stop.

01:25:36.920 --> 01:25:38.640
Take the next left.

01:25:45.080 --> 01:25:47.440
Turn off the lights.

01:25:54.720 --> 01:25:56.760
I had
a nice time tonight.

01:26:03.520 --> 01:26:05.920
The last guy
I went out with,

01:26:05.960 --> 01:26:07.720
you know what he did?

01:26:07.760 --> 01:26:10.520
He ditched me.

01:26:10.560 --> 01:26:13.440
He got up to go
to the men's room,

01:26:13.480 --> 01:26:15.440
never came back.

01:26:17.000 --> 01:26:20.560
Stuck me with the check.

01:26:20.600 --> 01:26:22.960
Never said goodbye.

01:26:23.000 --> 01:26:25.920
Never called
to apologize.

01:26:25.960 --> 01:26:29.360
He wasn't my type anyway.
He was a big-shot CPA.

01:26:29.400 --> 01:26:32.760
Super normal guy.
Didn't want to be dating some psycho.

01:26:40.160 --> 01:26:42.280
But you seem like
a nice person.

01:27:09.960 --> 01:27:12.640
Better not tell on me.

01:27:15.760 --> 01:27:17.680
You hear me?

01:27:21.320 --> 01:27:23.840
You better not tell,
or I'll fucking get you.

01:28:22.160 --> 01:28:24.840
Hold on, Mom.
Hold on, Dad.

01:28:24.880 --> 01:28:28.360
You should park the car
on the escalator, and back...

01:28:28.400 --> 01:28:30.720
- So?
- What?

01:28:30.760 --> 01:28:34.560
- Up, down and then up.
- Test, dummy. How'd it go?

01:28:34.600 --> 01:28:36.480
It was all right.

01:28:38.560 --> 01:28:40.520
You didn't call home
last night.

01:28:40.560 --> 01:28:42.120
I was worried.

01:28:42.160 --> 01:28:44.160
Go on the escalator.

01:28:44.200 --> 01:28:46.160
Guess I could really use
that cellphone.

01:28:47.480 --> 01:28:52.120
Go on the escalator.

01:29:19.680 --> 01:29:22.360
- Well, look who's back.
- Oh, hi.

01:29:22.400 --> 01:29:24.640
Hi, Jean.

01:29:24.680 --> 01:29:26.560
Thanks.

01:29:26.600 --> 01:29:28.440
You're a lifesaver.

01:29:28.480 --> 01:29:30.360
So how was
your old roommate?

01:29:30.400 --> 01:29:31.720
Oh, great.

01:29:31.720 --> 01:29:34.520
Yeah, thanks for doing this
on such short notice.

01:29:34.560 --> 01:29:37.800
Let me give you something
for your time.

01:29:37.800 --> 01:29:40.040
That's not necessary.

01:29:40.040 --> 01:29:43.280
No, really.
I insist.

01:29:44.560 --> 01:29:46.120
Please don't.

01:29:49.200 --> 01:29:50.760
Okay.

01:29:50.800 --> 01:29:53.000
Uh, any calls?

01:29:53.040 --> 01:29:54.560
Nope,
it was very quiet.

01:29:54.600 --> 01:29:57.920
She's asleep on your bed.
It was a very busy day.

01:29:57.960 --> 01:29:59.720
That's great.

01:29:59.760 --> 01:30:02.720
Um, Jean,
is everything okay?

01:30:06.040 --> 01:30:08.480
Yeah, she's
a wonderful child.

01:30:26.920 --> 01:30:28.840
Mommy.

01:30:39.400 --> 01:30:41.320
Mommy!

01:30:42.440 --> 01:30:44.000
Yeah.

01:30:44.040 --> 01:30:46.320
Are you coming?

01:30:49.840 --> 01:30:53.240
- I have something.
- What?

01:30:53.280 --> 01:30:55.320
I have something
for you.

01:30:59.400 --> 01:31:01.640
Just give me
a second here, okay?

01:31:28.160 --> 01:31:30.200
Brad.

01:31:34.520 --> 01:31:36.880
Brad.

01:31:37.960 --> 01:31:39.840
Hmm.

01:31:41.480 --> 01:31:44.440
Aaron's been telling me
about his new friend Lucy.

01:31:45.400 --> 01:31:47.880
She sounds like
a sweet little girl.

01:31:49.320 --> 01:31:51.280
What's her mother like?

01:31:55.480 --> 01:31:58.680
Nice enough, I guess.

01:31:58.720 --> 01:32:01.000
I can't even
remember her name.

01:32:04.680 --> 01:32:06.720
Isn't it Sarah?

01:32:08.040 --> 01:32:10.600
Sarah?

01:32:10.640 --> 01:32:12.920
Yeah, Sarah,

01:32:12.960 --> 01:32:14.520
from the pool.

01:32:14.560 --> 01:32:17.680
Her daughter's name
is Lucy.

01:32:17.720 --> 01:32:20.040
Oh, Lucy's mom.
Yeah, I forgot. That's right.

01:32:20.040 --> 01:32:22.720
Her name is Sarah.

01:32:22.760 --> 01:32:25.800
Hmm.

01:32:25.840 --> 01:32:27.920
Yeah, it might be
really nice for Aaron

01:32:27.960 --> 01:32:31.040
if they came over
for dinner.

01:32:34.840 --> 01:32:36.840
Okay.

01:32:58.880 --> 01:33:01.320
So you're
in advertising?

01:33:01.360 --> 01:33:04.080
No, that's-- that's
a common misconception.

01:33:04.120 --> 01:33:06.040
I'm not in advertising.
I'm in branding.

01:33:06.080 --> 01:33:08.080
And that's very different.

01:33:08.120 --> 01:33:10.160
Richard's pretty high up
in the company.

01:33:10.200 --> 01:33:12.080
Yeah yeah,
I have these clients

01:33:12.120 --> 01:33:13.800
and they'll come to me
when they have,

01:33:13.840 --> 01:33:16.040
you know, a new product
they wanna sell.

01:33:16.040 --> 01:33:19.320
Like, um, these guys,
they were in a couple weeks ago.

01:33:19.360 --> 01:33:22.280
They're trying to open this chain
of Chinese restaurants, right?

01:33:22.320 --> 01:33:25.640
They're talking to me
and I-- I look down at the table

01:33:25.640 --> 01:33:27.880
and I realize that none
of these guys were Chinese.

01:33:27.920 --> 01:33:30.760
Where were they from?

01:33:30.760 --> 01:33:32.800
They're a bunch of fat cats
from Tennessee.

01:33:32.840 --> 01:33:35.400
They think they can start a chain
of Chinese restaurants good enough

01:33:35.440 --> 01:33:37.320
to fool the average
American boob.

01:33:37.360 --> 01:33:39.320
Oh, God.

01:33:39.360 --> 01:33:41.840
Mmm!

01:33:41.880 --> 01:33:43.720
- This is delicious.
- Isn't it?

01:33:43.760 --> 01:33:46.240
Brad's a fantastic cook.

01:33:46.280 --> 01:33:49.480
So you guys see these
fliers with the guy's face

01:33:49.520 --> 01:33:51.280
plastered all over
our village?

01:33:51.320 --> 01:33:53.800
Lots of Sturm und Drang
in our quiet little town, huh?

01:33:53.840 --> 01:33:55.440
Yeah, it's crazy.

01:33:55.480 --> 01:33:57.920
What I want to know is why they let
a creep like that out of prison.

01:33:57.960 --> 01:34:00.680
Some of the people
going after him are just as crazy.

01:34:00.720 --> 01:34:03.560
- What do you mean?
- Well, just today I heard that

01:34:03.600 --> 01:34:05.680
some nut's been spray-painting
the poor guy's house,

01:34:05.720 --> 01:34:08.840
lighting fires on his porch.
God knows what else.

01:34:08.840 --> 01:34:10.760
- Do they know who's doing it?
- Huh-uh.

01:34:10.760 --> 01:34:12.680
They think
it's some ex-cop.

01:34:12.680 --> 01:34:14.680
You know, that guy
who killed that kid at the mall.

01:34:14.720 --> 01:34:16.400
Yeah, I don't think
it's him.

01:34:16.440 --> 01:34:19.080
You're biased.
You're friends with the guy.

01:34:19.080 --> 01:34:22.000
Brad's on that Committee
of Concerned Parents

01:34:22.040 --> 01:34:23.600
with him.

01:34:23.640 --> 01:34:25.400
I didn't know
you were on that.

01:34:25.440 --> 01:34:27.840
I play on his
football team.

01:34:27.880 --> 01:34:30.960
He asked me to distribute
some fliers.

01:34:31.000 --> 01:34:32.960
He's on your team.

01:34:33.000 --> 01:34:35.840
You never told me that.

01:34:35.880 --> 01:34:37.480
Yeah.

01:34:39.720 --> 01:34:43.200
You know what's weird?
I've never even seen this McGorvey guy.

01:34:43.240 --> 01:34:45.400
- We did.
- No, we didn't.

01:34:45.440 --> 01:34:47.360
Not you.
Me and Brad.

01:34:47.400 --> 01:34:50.320
That day at the pool,
remember?

01:34:50.360 --> 01:34:53.480
Yeah, I-I
totally forgot.

01:34:55.440 --> 01:34:58.560
- Well, what happened?
- Sexual tension is an elusive thing,

01:34:58.600 --> 01:35:00.840
but Kathy had
pretty good radar for it.

01:35:00.840 --> 01:35:04.320
It was like someone had
turned a knob a hair to the right,

01:35:04.360 --> 01:35:06.800
and the radio station
clicked in so loud and clear

01:35:06.840 --> 01:35:09.480
it almost
knocked her over.

01:35:09.520 --> 01:35:11.880
Once she became aware
of the connection between them,

01:35:11.880 --> 01:35:14.880
it seemed impossible that
she'd missed it before.

01:35:14.920 --> 01:35:17.440
On a hunch,
Kathy dropped her fork

01:35:17.480 --> 01:35:19.600
in the hopes that
while retrieving it

01:35:19.640 --> 01:35:22.880
she would catch Sarah
and Brad playing footsie,

01:35:22.920 --> 01:35:25.160
- but she was mistaken.
- Asked him to leave, and he left.

01:35:25.200 --> 01:35:28.360
But you know what?
He didn't look scary, right? I mean--

01:35:28.360 --> 01:35:31.080
No, it-- it wasn't that big
of a deal, you know.

01:35:31.120 --> 01:35:33.720
- No, he's like a regular guy, you know?
- Yeah, I mean--

01:35:33.760 --> 01:35:35.680
Kathy, are you okay?

01:35:35.720 --> 01:35:37.560
Uh, yeah.

01:35:37.600 --> 01:35:40.600
Just a sec.

01:35:40.640 --> 01:35:42.240
Brad had convinced
himself

01:35:42.280 --> 01:35:44.640
the dinner party
had gone well.

01:35:44.680 --> 01:35:48.040
That he and Sarah had managed
to put Kathy's suspicions to rest,

01:35:48.080 --> 01:35:50.200
at least temporarily.

01:35:50.240 --> 01:35:52.360
She certainly hadn't
accused him of anything,

01:35:52.360 --> 01:35:54.280
or behaved in a way
that made him think

01:35:54.280 --> 01:35:56.240
she'd noticed
anything untoward.

01:36:01.280 --> 01:36:04.640
I'm really glad
they came over.

01:36:10.160 --> 01:36:12.960
- Good night.
- Good night.

01:36:13.000 --> 01:36:14.640
Two days later, however,

01:36:14.680 --> 01:36:16.880
his mother-in-law showed up
for a surprise visit...

01:36:16.920 --> 01:36:19.720
- Thank you, John.
- ...of ominously indeterminate length.

01:36:19.760 --> 01:36:22.440
And from that moment on,
she accompanied Brad

01:36:22.480 --> 01:36:24.200
and Aaron everywhere:

01:36:24.200 --> 01:36:26.000
To the playground;

01:36:26.040 --> 01:36:28.840
- We need some butter.
- To the supermarket;

01:36:28.880 --> 01:36:31.280
And to the town pool.

01:36:31.320 --> 01:36:33.880
Hi, Aaron.

01:36:33.920 --> 01:36:37.080
Hi, Lucy.

01:36:38.440 --> 01:36:41.120
The worst of it
was the pool.

01:36:41.160 --> 01:36:43.720
Nevertheless,
after threatening all week

01:36:43.760 --> 01:36:46.920
to go the football game,
Brad's mother-in-law decided against it

01:36:46.920 --> 01:36:48.840
at the last minute.

01:36:48.840 --> 01:36:50.840
- So are you coming?
- Well, I'd like to,

01:36:50.880 --> 01:36:52.760
but I'm a little tired.

01:36:52.800 --> 01:36:55.040
You sure?
You're welcome to.

01:36:55.080 --> 01:36:56.960
No, go ahead.
You and Aaron

01:36:57.000 --> 01:36:59.160
sure kept me hopping
this afternoon.

01:36:59.200 --> 01:37:01.200
Looks like
you're on your own.

01:37:01.240 --> 01:37:04.080
Oh, that's my ride.

01:37:04.120 --> 01:37:06.760
- What time are you gonna be home?
- I don't know.

01:37:06.760 --> 01:37:08.440
Pretty late, though.

01:37:08.480 --> 01:37:11.320
Be careful and stay
out of trouble.

01:37:23.920 --> 01:37:26.320
Winds whisper
of high hopes,

01:37:26.360 --> 01:37:28.400
victory is in the skies.

01:37:28.440 --> 01:37:31.680
One joins with many
on the summer's green field.

01:37:31.720 --> 01:37:34.760
At 0 and 5, the Guardians
were the basement dwellers

01:37:34.760 --> 01:37:37.480
of the Tri-County
Touch Football Night League.

01:37:37.520 --> 01:37:41.240
The Controllers, a team of young
hotshots from the financial district

01:37:41.280 --> 01:37:44.040
were 4 and 1
with an explosive offense

01:37:44.080 --> 01:37:47.240
that regularly racked up
40 to 50 points a game.

01:37:47.240 --> 01:37:49.280
But from
the opening kickoff,

01:37:49.320 --> 01:37:52.680
this ragtag group
of law enforcement officers

01:37:52.720 --> 01:37:54.840
decided to crunch
their own numbers.

01:37:58.400 --> 01:38:00.600
But the Controllers
scored first

01:38:00.640 --> 01:38:02.560
after recovering
a Bart Williams fumble

01:38:02.600 --> 01:38:06.360
deep in Guardians' territory near
the end of the second quarter.

01:38:10.920 --> 01:38:13.880
The Guardians evened things up early
in the second half...

01:38:15.640 --> 01:38:17.800
moving methodically
downfield

01:38:17.800 --> 01:38:19.960
on an 80-yard
touchdown drive.

01:38:24.800 --> 01:38:27.880
The Controllers regained the lead
with a fourth quarter field goal.

01:38:27.920 --> 01:38:31.400
With less than a minute
to go, trailing by three,

01:38:31.440 --> 01:38:33.400
the Guardians faced
the extinction of their hopes.

01:38:33.440 --> 01:38:35.840
- Down!
- It was their last chance--

01:38:35.880 --> 01:38:38.280
4th and 5
on their own 35.

01:38:38.280 --> 01:38:41.000
Set!

01:38:41.000 --> 01:38:43.640
Hut, hut!

01:39:15.080 --> 01:39:18.080
Yeah yeah yeah!

01:39:18.120 --> 01:39:23.280
Yeah yeah!

01:39:24.520 --> 01:39:27.040
Yeah!

01:39:28.120 --> 01:39:29.600
Oh my God!

01:39:29.640 --> 01:39:32.520
Yeah!

01:39:42.000 --> 01:39:45.040
Brad, Brad!

01:39:46.120 --> 01:39:47.680
What do you want?

01:39:47.720 --> 01:39:51.200
Everyone is waiting for us at the bar.
Are-- are-- are you coming?

01:39:51.240 --> 01:39:53.360
Why don't you go on ahead?
I'll catch up later.

01:39:53.400 --> 01:39:55.920
You're gonna come, right?
I mean, we gotta celebrate.

01:39:55.960 --> 01:39:57.600
Yeah yeah yeah,
